I am not yet very experienced with babl but from your first comment I read that this should be the way to go

```
static void
ubyte332_to_rgba (const Babl *conversion,
                  const char *src,
                  char       *dst,
                  long        n,
                  void       *user_data);

static void
rgba_to_ubyte332 (const Babl *conversion,
                  const char *src,
                  char       *dst,
                  long        n,
                  void       *user_data);

static void
init (void)
{
  const Babl *fmt, *base;

  base = babl_format ("RGBA double");
  fmt  = babl_format_new ("name",
                          "R 3u G 3u B 2u",
                          babl_model ("RGB"),
                          babl_component ("R"),
                          babl_component ("G"),
                          babl_component ("B"),
                          NULL);
  babl_conversion_new (fmt, base, "linear", ubyte332_to_rgba, NULL);
  babl_conversion_new (base, fmt, "linear", rgba_to_ubyte332, NULL);
}
```

Is that correct? Then I will start implementing these conversions and feed them back to this project when ready.

Kind regards,
FeBrex

